# NPC Design Goals

NPCs should feel **intentional and believable**, not robotic. Behavior emerges from simple interacting rules.

## NPCs Should Have
- Goals, needs, routines
- Emotional states, relationships
- Motivations: hunger, fear, loyalty, prestige, family protection, revenge

## Improvement Examples
- Goal-based behavior, memory of events
- Reacting to danger, social alliances
- Group hunting coordination
- "NPC remembers who helped during hunts → trusts them more"
- Hunters who bring back food gain prestige

## Avoid
Simple "walk up and attack." Hunting should feel risky and strategic (tracking, awareness, ambush, wounded animals fleeing).
